  "description": "Growing protocol for *Barbarea verna* (land cress), cool-season biennial producing watercress-like peppery leaves without requiring flowing water. Seed exhibits thermodormancy below 70°F only; sow in fall or early spring. Hardy to -20°F; matures in 50–60 days under cool conditions. Perennial in zones 5–9.",
